appy.  That translates to approximately 50 pts of ATK, which will raise both paladins hit percentage and damage per hit.  It wont be a significant change, but I think thats all paladins need.<br><br>Olvan Anvildawn<br>Crusader<br>Tribunal Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 766<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 1:10:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14839.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: After the smoke all clears about whatwe deserve and need</span><hr size=1> They already did raise our offensive abilities substantially by putting us on the war damage table.<br>Dual wield is absolutely out of the question. way too overpowering.<br><br>I don't understand this at all:<br>59 94% &lt;&lt;&lt;--- close enough to cleric to not get the &quot;No thanks I'll wait for a couple hours and see if a cleric shows up.&quot;<br><br>Do you care that someone turns down your res??? If they think they can inch out that extra 6% on the 11% they lost by waiting an extra hour for a res then who cares. extra mana for you.... No reason for us to get anything higher than 90%. <br><br>Do people not understand the concept of hybrid not being as good at everything their parent class is good at? We have a mix of abilities of both classes. Not all the abilities of both classes. We would be a dual class then. not a hybrid. If you wanna give us all the abilities of both you'd have to cap paladins at L55 or something to make up for it.<br><br>I dunno, too much complaining about we need this we need that these days. Look into the light.....paladins are good. There's a few things that could be reworked, but defensive, CH,  dual wield are not in the books. Don't ask for them because they are far too powerful with respect to all of the other classes in the game.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utelumehtar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telumehtar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 2:16:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14839.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: After the smoke all clears about whatwe deserve and need</span><hr size=1> Personally I like the upcoming Rez changes.  That right there will be a boon.<br><br>Making ToK and AE stun would suit me just fine or to be honest if left alone I wouldn't be bothered.<br><br>The two things I think should be reviewed and fixed are our two discs.<br><br>I would like to dump Holyforge all together.  Its annoying kicking on a disc then not seeing even 1 crit or crip go off and it happens way to often that way.  Couple that with the fact that it breaks when you get the AA crit skill its just all sorts of messed up.<br><br>Move Sanctification to 55.  Its an ok disc and has its uses even if limited.<br><br>At 60 give us a half duration Defensive disc OR give us an Auto-parry disc comparable to rangers.  This would give us some defensive ability to appropriately match our role as a defensive hybrid.<br><br>Anyhow if they did just those two things to our disc and didn't do anything else I would be fully content with my paladin.  I love this class and all the rest of what it brings but when the only disc worthwhile to use is that Resistance disc everyone gets then its just a little frustrating. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span 